A multi-faceted law enforcement operation took place in Ivory Park in Ekurhuleni. Several arrests were made during the operation. Reporter Michael Appel has more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A range of law enforcement operations has targeted the crime hotspot of Ivory Park in Ekurhuleni. Gauteng Police Commissioner Elias Mawela, was on the ground, overseeing and participating in what police call - 'stamping the authority of the state'. READ: No arrests yet as police investigate Shallcross murders "In a roadblock, we have already recovered four identified stolen vehicles where the VIN and chassis numbers were tampered with," said Commissioner Mawela. Mawela said they have embarked on an awareness and educational campaign. READ: SA Lockdown: Cele's stern warning Police made several arrests during the operation. Watch the video above for more on this story.